content: It is not specified in the provided text what the decision in the case of F v M was. The text only mentions that the father, F, made an application for a Child Arrangements Order for contact with both children, despite never having met the youngest child, and an application for a Specific Issue Order to change the youngest child's surname and that the mother's legal team made applications for permission to disclose the judgment and case papers to the police and to remove F's Parental Responsibility.
